The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will constitute a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day when the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway traffic will stop completely and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday, which will be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists that will coordinate the actions of Monday will also be constituted.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will go on strike indefinitely, if an agreement is not reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike action.
Instead, if the law is passed, strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of Monday’s agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on in the late-night hours, or perhaps around midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: railways will stop working indefinitely, in the morning part of the Budapest public transport and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the Volán companies may stop.
Simultaneously, in many parts of the country there will be closure of half of the roads.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names being constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some unions announced their strike for an indefinite period, others for a definite period.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, the Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 in the morning, will hold a four-hour strike the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical and Thermal Energy Industry, the Trade Unions of Educators called a strike of 2 and the Democratic Trade Union of Educators 8.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will take a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS), which is part of the Forum of Trade Union Cooperation, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is for the government to withdraw its public health reform proposal and submit a new conception to social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new way of calculating pensions that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions, the possibility that occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, from various points of view has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions existing between the Roma and non-Roma population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life ceded the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts erupting.
In addition to that, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially as regards the stability and democratic development of the country."
