This would reduce consumption and send the American economy into recession with different impacts on the growth of the world economy.
The central banks thus decided, after they failed to reduce the so-called LIBOR rate, London interbank rate that is used for the loan of money in the interbank market.
This means that banks were constantly afraid to lend themselves money even when the central banks of the US, Canada and Britain lowered their interest rates several times during the fall.
