600,000 people failed to change their driver’s license
Six hundred thousand drivers were passed the date and therefore did not manage to change their old driver's license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials can give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that after New Year there will be hundreds of thousands of drivers on the roads without a valid driver’s license.
According to traffic, the license has not changed mainly those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline of the change of card, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and the interest for the new card has increased.
The City Council estimates around 2,000 customers per day.
In the queues wait half an hour.
Around 140,000 drivers have not yet been issued a new driving licence in Prague.
The issuance of a new card lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their license and do not reach the end of the year, but will go out on the roads without a valid card will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand kroner.
The officer can fix the violation with a reprimand.
If it is an administrative offence, the fine will amount to 2,500 kroner.
According to the above information, a person who does not go anywhere could receive a fine.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 kroner.
The Ministry appealed to the offices for moderate fines of up to 1,000 kroner.
According to Karel Hanzelka, a spokesman for the transport ministry, fines of 1,000 crowns do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driver’s license is a document in which people can decide whether they want it or not.
