And it is where one of the panels, which unfold like accordions, has been damaged in a little more or less than a meter by a cable that was jammed.
The deployment has been stopped so as not to damage the panel further.
The astronauts, who had initially to make a control exit from the shuttle Discovery, and then go to repair another solar panel whose rotation system was defective, were forced to devote themselves to the damaged panel.
