Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
In parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by the Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets work efficiently.
The MIFID, which modifies the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow the provision of financial advisory services to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management practices to the market and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they undertake, to facilitate oversight by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Economy Committee of Congress, several modifications were incorporated, among which it stands out that the securitised debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of US subprime mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that can be performed by graduates in Economics and Business 30 years after the Royal Decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for others, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment companies at the same time.
