What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in case of possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for that reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics reflect that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
In addition, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and with it the probability of having some type of mishap.
Increasing the frequency increases the odds.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why, the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face several disadvantages when it comes to taking out insurance at an affordable price, such as limited driving experience and the age of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk with franchise, so that they get the coverages of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would mean that the customer pays a part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer contributes will be pre-established based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount", specifies Luis Noguera, head in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, but not against those caused in their own car.
In addition, it would be covered for theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years old, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, and may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
In contrast, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fee.
"Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the company's profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses,” Noguera said.
After the age of 25, drivers have it easier to take out insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to take an all-risk franchise.
"Normally young people can not make use of the experience previously acquired when making use of an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows it, of course.
On the other hand, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with a deductible (this could be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They have a more relaxed driving style and they have more purchasing power to afford to take on a larger franchise amount,” says Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is recommended an all-risk insurance with franchise (being this one of 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in case of possible claims, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
