The reunion and the world tour coincide with the release of a new album that includes their main hits as well as two new songs, 'Headlines' and 'Voodoo', which EMI publishes in Spain.
The five Spice Girls members took to the stage wearing bracelets given to them by 'Posh Spice's' husband, British footballer David Beckham.
