Beckham said the British star "hasn't seen our costumes at all, so I'm nervous about what he's going to think of the show."
Sporty Spice, whose departure from the group in 1998 "because of the differences between us" caused the dissolution of the quintet two years later, also expressed his nervousness during a meeting with the press, two hours before the start of the show.
“I was scared.
I was nervous but I saw that the feeling of the world has changed, the feeling for the Spice Girls has changed.
And I thought why not, so I’m glad I made the decision,” Chisholm said of the group’s reunion she disbanded nine years ago.
The singer also noted that over time, "things have been fixed and we all love each other very much."
But much has changed since the Spice Girls last performed together in 1998.
For starters, according to CTV television, the group arrived in Vancouver on a special Virgin Airlines plane.
Upon arrival at the airport, an army of nannies was waiting for them.
Among the five are seven children.
