Actress Judi Dench was named best actress for the thriller "Notes from a Scandal."
And Bond star Daniel Craig won the Variety Award for putting a British film on the international stage.
The awards were presented at a ceremony at London’s Roundhouse.
Control follows Curtis' rise to fame with Joy Division, until his suicide in 1980, at the age of 23.
The black-and-white film, which features soundtracks from The Killers, David Bowie and New Order, was produced for just <0xC2><0xA3>3,000.
