In January 2004, Fastow was convicted of two counts of conspiracy in the Enron collapse.
The trio of Britons were arrested three months later.
Fastow is serving a 6-year sentence in a Louisiana federal prison.
Kopper is serving a three-year, one-month sentence in Texarkana.
Each of the three British bankers was required to pay $1 million to live in the United States while the trial was taking place.
