The two films "The Hunting Party" and "Moerderischer Frieden" are again dedicated to the war in the Balkans.
But the two didn’t have much conviction.
Either the concepts are very fixated on actions and shootings or the two films are too exciting.
Richard Gere with his "The Hunting Party" can't help in this case either.
At first there was good news: Karadzic and Mladic, the war criminals, are still hiding in the mountain of the Balkans, but precisely there, in the dark interior of the country during the Bosnian War, the actor Richard Gere was discovered again.
