The film is like the German series "Alarm for Cobra 11" without a highway, but in a war situation.
In the example of "The Hunting Party" you can investigate, because in reality there was never a good film about the war in the Balkans.
At another time, with another director and another scriptwriter (Richard Shepard on two counts), the story about American reporters in the war leaving to spot a Serbian war criminal named “fox” could probably be a new “Apocalypse Now.”
Thus, the stories are surprisingly similar: the small teams go to the mountain twice to carry out something that the army can not do and each time it turns out to be a crazy trip.
