It's not the wooden boxes.
Whoever relates the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Currently the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on the list of Warhol’s works.
Most of the ninety-four Brillo-type boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" cast doubt on the authenticity of Andy Warhol's 1968 Brillo-Boxes, the Moderna Museet Museum in Stockholm conducted internal research and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former director of the Pontus Hultén Museum also gave to the Moderna Museet Museum, are fake, and came to disappointing conclusions.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Brillo-Boxes", painted the wooden boxes red, blue and white, with the same sample that had cardboards of soap powder "Brillo".
According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his 1968 works at the Museet Moderna were exposed hundreds of Gloss-cardboard boxes. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the cardboard factory of "Brillo".
These were not works of art, but examples (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed to produce in Sweden a Gloss-wood boxes, but they were not exhibited in the Modern Museet museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Brillo-Boxes" of "Stockholm type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the museum Pontus Hultén made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exposed almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malm<0xC3><0xB6> for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already been dead for 3 years.
Lars Bystr<0xC3><0xB6>m, the head of the curators of the Museet Moderna, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First their tight silvers were printed and ground down and then oil-painted with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies of the year 1990 shows that the paint was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. In addition it is not oil paint, but acrylic paint.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and should be removed from the official list of Andy Warhol’s Brillo-Boxes,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Museet Moderna museum and adds that if the “Andy Warhol Art” Authentication Commission in New York does not reach some conclusion, the Museet Moderna museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/objects of exhibition.”
Already in July, the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" in the case of boxes of soap powder.
But from that moment on, everything remained absolutely silent.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers who had barricaded themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the downfall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered.
Chief Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president on corruption and election fraud, told a reporter he could not answer for shedding blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had stormed the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had barricaded themselves for a few hours in the building.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, had a trial on Thursday for attempting a coup in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, to suddenly be able to deposit with about 30 sympathizers.
Evidently the military policemen who were to watch over him had passed into their ranks and continued their mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blockaded the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called for an urgent meeting of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the national security adviser, condemned the soldiers’ behavior.
"People are fed up," Trillanes said.
“We invite people to join our ranks.”
Gen. Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said that before long the other military troops wanted to continue the march.
Big government critics called for a big demonstration against the president on Thursday.
For months his government has been accused of corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986 there have been at least seven attempted coups against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price per share is 14.46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial part at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after bank Brendenberg increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution holds the equity securities for a third party partner.
United Internet already the previous day made the telecommunication company Drillisch participate with almost 10 percent.
Drillisch in the capital increase measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares of them for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on DSL-product marketing cooperation.
"We are strengthening our collaboration," United Internet said in a statement.
The two companies founded a joint venture, MSP, to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday United Internet reported that at the start, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they do participate in 18.49 percent of Freenet.
That meant that both companies retained all options, especially the stake in the Freenet corporation.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
So far the holding company of United Internet and Drillisch directly held 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch would get the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of investment firm Vatas was already agreed in August.
